Frequently Asked Questions for Deckers Outdoor Corporation (NYSE:DECK)
What is Deckers Outdoor Corporation's stock symbol?

Deckers Outdoor Corporation trades on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) under the ticker symbol "DECK."



How were Deckers Outdoor Corporation's earnings last quarter?

Deckers Outdoor Corporation (NYSE:DECK) released its earnings results on Thursday, July, 27th. The company reported ($1.28) earnings per share for the quarter, topping analysts' consensus estimates of ($1.67) by $0.39. The business had revenue of $209.70 million for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $178.36 million. Deckers Outdoor Corporation had a return on equity of 12.48% and a net margin of 0.32%. The business's revenue was up 20.2% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same quarter last year, the firm posted ($1.80) earnings per share.  View Deckers Outdoor Corporation's Earnings History.



What guidance has Deckers Outdoor Corporation issued on next quarter's earnings?

Deckers Outdoor Corporation issued an update on its FY18 earnings guidance on Thursday, July, 27th. The company provided earnings per share guidance of $3.95-4.15 for the period, compared to the Thomson Reuters consensus EPS estimate of $4.04. Deckers Outdoor Corporation also updated its Q2 guidance to $1.00-1.05 EPS.



Where is Deckers Outdoor Corporation's stock going? Where will Deckers Outdoor Corporation's stock price be in 2017?

16 brokers have issued 12 month price objectives for Deckers Outdoor Corporation's stock. Their forecasts range from $52.00 to $80.00. On average, they expect Deckers Outdoor Corporation's stock price to reach $65.69 in the next year. View Analyst Ratings for Deckers Outdoor Corporation.



What are analysts saying about Deckers Outdoor Corporation stock?

Here are some recent quotes from research analysts about Deckers Outdoor Corporation stock: 
1. According to Zacks Investment Research, "Deckers ended fiscal 2017 on a high note as this footwear retailer surprised investors by posting profit in the final quarter and beating the Zacks Consensus mark by a wide margin. Top line also came ahead of our estimate, after missing the same in the preceding two quarters. Better-than-expected results and an upbeat fiscal 2018 earnings projection were enough to propel the stock further that has outpaced the industry in the past three months. However, top line continues to decline year over year and management now expects fiscal 2018 net sales to be flat to down 2%. Nevertheless, the company’s focus on expanding brand assortments, innovative line of products and optimizing omni-channel distribution bode well. We believe Deckers’ long-term target of $2 billion sales with operating margin of 13% by fiscal 2020 seem achievable. However, analysts believe that the company’s over-reliance on the UGG brand is a matter of concern." (6/1/2017)
2. Canaccord Genuity analysts commented, "We remain positive on DECK heading into FQ4 results on Thursday, May 25 AMC. We are projecting EPS of -2c vs. -6c consensus. Given the activist involvement, we believe FQ4 is largely inconsequential to the stock from a sales/EPS perspective. In our opinion, the most important driver for the stock continues to be the ongoing exploration of strategic alternatives. Recall, the company last month formally announced a strategic review, which includes the possibility of a sale of the business. In our note following the announcement (link here) we estimated a fair value takeout price for DECK approximates $75/share. That said, we are not likely to get many progress updates of the strategic review until it is complete. As such, we anticipate the focus will turn to the fundamentals of the business, centered on two key factors: (1) the backlog/sales growth guidance, and (2) the expense savings initiatives. Despite challenges in the US wholesale channel, our industry checks suggest orders for UGGs could be flat to down slightly, a positive outcome in our view. We believe the new Classic line extensions (Classic 2, Slim, Luxe, Street) experienced strong sell-throughs this past winter season at w/s, boding well for orders. The bigger focus will be on the $150M in total cost savings DECK is pursuing and the potential for further margin-enhancing initiatives. We are modeling DECK to show a decline in SG&A dollar growth in F18 of $7M, which could be conservative. Overall, we believe the ongoing sale process, strengthening product line and cost savings initiatives provide ample idiosyncratic reasons to remain positive on the stock." (5/23/2017)




Who are some of Deckers Outdoor Corporation's key competitors?

 Some companies that are related to Deckers Outdoor Corporation include International Game Technology (IGT), Columbia Sportswear Company (COLM), Cedar Fair, L.P. (FUN), Under Armour (UA), Extended Stay America (STAY), Sinclair Broadcast Group (SBGI), Tribune Media Company (TRCO), Hilton Grand Vacations (HGV), Choice Hotels International (CHH), Grand Canyon Education (LOPE), Nord Anglia Education (NORD), ILG (ILG), Graham Holdings Company (GHC), TEGNA (TGNA), Zynga (ZNGA), Marriot Vacations Worldwide Corporation (VAC), Regal Entertainment Group (RGC) and Nexstar Broadcasting Group (NXST).



Who are Deckers Outdoor Corporation's key executives?

Deckers Outdoor Corporation's management team includes the folowing people: David A. Powers, Chief Executive Officer, DirectorThomas A. George CPA, Chief Financial OfficerStefano Caroti, President - Omni-ChannelAndrea O'Donnell, President - Fashion LifestyleDavid E. Lafitte, Chief Operating OfficerAngel R. Martinez, Non-Executive Chairman of the BoardJohn M. Gibbons, Lead Independent DirectorKaryn Odette Barsa, Independent DirectorNelson C. Chan, Independent DirectorMichael F. Devine III, Independent Director



Who owns Deckers Outdoor Corporation stock?

Deckers Outdoor Corporation's stock is owned by a variety of of retail and institutional investors. Top institutional investors include Dalton Greiner Hartman Maher & Co. (0.62%), Smith Graham & Co. Investment Advisors LP (0.58%), West Coast Financial LLC (0.23%), Tokio Marine Asset Management Co. Ltd. (0.16%), Acadian Asset Management LLC (0.11%) and Great West Life Assurance Co. Can (0.06%). Company insiders that own Deckers Outdoor Corporation stock include Angel R Martinez, David Powers, John G Perenchio and Karyn Odette Barsa. View Institutional Ownership Trends for Deckers Outdoor Corporation.



Who sold Deckers Outdoor Corporation stock? Who is selling Deckers Outdoor Corporation stock?

Deckers Outdoor Corporation's stock was sold by a variety of institutional investors in the last quarter, including Dalton Greiner Hartman Maher & Co., Rothschild Asset Management Inc., Smith Graham & Co. Investment Advisors LP, Russell Investments Group Ltd. and Municipal Employees Retirement System of Michigan. Company insiders that have sold Deckers Outdoor Corporation stock in the last year include Angel R Martinez, David Powers and John G Perenchio. View Insider Buying and Selling for Deckers Outdoor Corporation.



Who bought Deckers Outdoor Corporation stock? Who is buying Deckers Outdoor Corporation stock?

Deckers Outdoor Corporation's stock was acquired by a variety of institutional investors in the last quarter, including Acadian Asset Management LLC, Campbell & CO Investment Adviser LLC, Fox Run Management L.L.C., ING Groep NV, James Investment Research Inc., Tokio Marine Asset Management Co. Ltd., West Coast Financial LLC and NN Investment Partners Holdings N.V..  View Insider Buying and Selling for Deckers Outdoor Corporation.



How do I buy Deckers Outdoor Corporation stock? 

Shares of Deckers Outdoor Corporation can be purchased through any online brokerage account. Popular online brokerages include Vanguard Brokerage Services, TD Ameritrade, E*TRADE, Scottrade, Fidelity and Charles Schwab. 



What is Deckers Outdoor Corporation's stock price today?

One share of Deckers Outdoor Corporation stock can currently be purchased for approximately $64.41.


